00:16:25.300 --> 00:16:26.420
that I began to scratch my head.

00:16:26.420 --> 00:16:30.100
I sent an article to my Holly and the three kids.

00:16:30.100 --> 00:16:31.260
I sent an article to them and I said,

00:16:31.260 --> 00:16:33.500
man, look at what's going on right here.

00:16:33.500 --> 00:16:34.340
Why did I send it to them?

00:16:34.340 --> 00:16:36.100
Well, because we have a,

00:16:36.140 --> 00:16:38.980
an attempt at peace agreement that is very similar

00:16:38.980 --> 00:16:41.260
to what we're going to see Antichrist do

00:16:41.260 --> 00:16:43.660
at the start of the tribulation.

00:16:43.660 --> 00:16:45.100
It's with a different group of people,

00:16:45.100 --> 00:16:47.420
but there's a lot of similarities.

00:16:47.420 --> 00:16:49.540
You're seeing all sorts of crazy,

00:16:49.540 --> 00:16:52.260
our government shut down, right?

00:16:52.260 --> 00:16:53.700
Is that what's going on?

00:16:53.700 --> 00:16:55.020
And listen, if we're not careful,

00:16:55.020 --> 00:16:57.340
we get our eyes on all these other things

00:16:57.340 --> 00:17:00.180
and we get all kinds of frazzled and worked up.

00:17:00.180 --> 00:17:01.820
And I understand we have to,

00:17:01.820 --> 00:17:03.900
we have to get our eyes on the Lord.

00:17:03.940 --> 00:17:05.820
Because if we get our eyes on all those things,

00:17:05.820 --> 00:17:06.660
guess what?

00:17:06.660 --> 00:17:09.060
We're going to have all kinds of turmoil

00:17:09.060 --> 00:17:11.260
and we're going to have stress

00:17:11.260 --> 00:17:13.260
and we're going to have anxiety

00:17:13.260 --> 00:17:14.860
and we're going to be worrying

00:17:14.860 --> 00:17:16.500
and we're going to be fretting, right?

00:17:16.500 --> 00:17:18.500
And that's what's going to happen.

00:17:18.500 --> 00:17:20.780
So we got to get our eyes on the Lord.

00:17:20.780 --> 00:17:23.500
We find not only does he say that his soul,

00:17:23.500 --> 00:17:24.700
I lift up my soul,

00:17:24.700 --> 00:17:27.940
mine eyes are ever towards the Lord.

00:17:27.940 --> 00:17:30.660
We find not only does he say that his soul,

00:17:30.660 --> 00:17:31.900
I lift up my soul,

00:17:31.940 --> 00:17:34.540
mine eyes are ever toward the Lord.

00:17:34.540 --> 00:17:37.260
But notice as you continue reading in verse number 15,

00:17:37.260 --> 00:17:40.460
not only does David say mine eyes are ever toward the Lord,

00:17:40.460 --> 00:17:42.580
but notice what he says at the end of the verse,

00:17:42.580 --> 00:17:44.220
for he, that's the Lord,

00:17:44.220 --> 00:17:48.320
shall pluck my feet out of the net.

00:17:49.300 --> 00:17:53.020
So begins to use this imagery for us this evening

00:17:53.020 --> 00:17:58.020
where David is feeling like his feet are in a net,

00:17:58.100 --> 00:18:00.540
where he's in this trap.

00:18:00.540 --> 00:18:03.580
He's in this place of difficulty, of course,

00:18:03.580 --> 00:18:05.100
the need for direction,

00:18:05.100 --> 00:18:06.580
and we'll focus on that next week,

00:18:06.580 --> 00:18:07.820
but the need for peace.

00:18:07.820 --> 00:18:11.220
And we find that David mentions lifting up his soul.

00:18:11.220 --> 00:18:13.380
He mentions his eyes are toward the Lord.

00:18:13.380 --> 00:18:14.660
And he says, for he,

00:18:14.660 --> 00:18:19.660
the Lord shall pluck my feet out of the net.

00:18:19.700 --> 00:18:22.900
David's posture as we read through this Psalm

00:18:22.900 --> 00:18:26.140
reveals to us the distress in which he's dealing with.

00:18:26.140 --> 00:18:27.740
And we could understand tonight

00:18:28.540 --> 00:18:31.820
we too can deal with times of distress

00:18:31.820 --> 00:18:34.260
and our circumstances can be overwhelming

00:18:34.260 --> 00:18:36.500
to the point where we may not even be able

00:18:36.500 --> 00:18:38.559
to communicate with another human being,

00:18:38.559 --> 00:18:40.739
all that we're really dealing with.

00:18:41.580 --> 00:18:44.820
But God knows, and God cares,

00:18:44.820 --> 00:18:47.179
and God is the God of all comfort.

00:18:47.179 --> 00:18:51.540
He is Jehovah Shalom, as we studied a few weeks ago,

00:18:51.540 --> 00:18:54.340
that he does give peace.

00:18:54.340 --> 00:18:57.260
We understand the Lord Jesus Christ, Prince of Peace,

00:18:57.780 --> 00:19:00.220
and we'll look at some things with regard to the peace

00:19:00.220 --> 00:19:02.900
that God offers as we go throughout

00:19:02.900 --> 00:19:04.440
the remainder of the message.

00:19:04.440 --> 00:19:07.179
But we note, first of all, the distress of the psalmist.

00:19:07.179 --> 00:19:10.440
Then I want you to notice the desire of the psalmist,

00:19:10.440 --> 00:19:11.900
the desire of the psalmist.

00:19:11.900 --> 00:19:13.000
What is his desire?

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:15.920
Well, I believe that as you consider his posture,

00:19:15.920 --> 00:19:17.340
that it reveals his distress,

00:19:17.340 --> 00:19:20.020
but as you consider his plea,

00:19:20.020 --> 00:19:23.300
it reveals for us his desire.

00:19:23.300 --> 00:19:25.660
Notice again, in verse number two,

00:19:25.660 --> 00:19:29.140
he says, oh my God, I trust in thee.

00:19:29.140 --> 00:19:30.540
And then notice this phrase,

00:19:30.540 --> 00:19:32.420
and he'll use this phrase a couple of times

00:19:32.420 --> 00:19:36.380
throughout the psalm, let me not be ashamed.

00:19:36.380 --> 00:19:39.540
Let not my enemies triumph over me.

00:19:39.540 --> 00:19:44.380
Verse three, yea, let none that wait on thee be ashamed.

00:19:44.380 --> 00:19:48.980
Let them be ashamed which transgress without cause.

00:19:48.980 --> 00:19:50.820
And so we find in verse number two,

00:19:50.820 --> 00:19:53.580
he says, let me not be ashamed.

00:19:53.580 --> 00:19:54.860
In verse number three, he says,

00:19:54.860 --> 00:19:57.980
yea, let none that wait on thee be ashamed.

00:19:57.980 --> 00:20:00.020
David was trusting the Lord.

00:20:00.020 --> 00:20:01.420
according to verse number two.

00:20:01.420 --> 00:20:04.660
He was waiting on the Lord according to verse number three.

00:20:04.660 --> 00:20:07.500
And I believe that that idea of waiting on the Lord

00:20:07.500 --> 00:20:10.580
carries with it a couple of different ideas.

00:20:10.580 --> 00:20:14.380
One of them is to wait, to be still and know that I am God

00:20:14.380 --> 00:20:16.020
and that type of waiting.

00:20:16.020 --> 00:20:18.340
But there's also the aspect of serving the Lord,

00:20:18.340 --> 00:20:20.980
waiting on the Lord and serving him.

00:20:20.980 --> 00:20:23.420
And we find that David is in the midst of doing

00:20:23.420 --> 00:20:26.500
both of those things during this particular time.

00:20:26.500 --> 00:20:28.700
And he says, let me not be ashamed.

00:20:28.740 --> 00:20:31.020
He mentions it again in verse number 19,

00:20:31.020 --> 00:20:33.940
when he says, consider mine enemies for there are many

00:20:33.940 --> 00:20:36.940
and they hate me with cruel hatred.

00:20:36.940 --> 00:20:40.820
Verse 20, he says, oh, keep my soul and deliver me.

00:20:40.820 --> 00:20:45.820
Let me not be ashamed for I put my trust in thee.

00:20:46.860 --> 00:20:50.540
By the way, we understand that as we look at this Psalm

00:20:50.540 --> 00:20:55.020
and we think about the series that we just concluded,

00:20:55.020 --> 00:20:58.180
there's references here where David says,

00:20:58.180 --> 00:21:00.700
I'm trusting in the Lord.

00:21:00.700 --> 00:21:03.100
He knew who God was.

00:21:03.100 --> 00:21:04.860
He knew what God was able to do.

00:21:04.860 --> 00:21:07.660
He knew what God could provide for him

00:21:07.660 --> 00:21:10.620
that no other person could provide for him.

00:21:10.620 --> 00:21:15.620
And David was placing purposefully, I trust in thee.

00:21:16.020 --> 00:21:17.860
He says there in verse number two.

00:21:17.860 --> 00:21:22.620
In verse number 20, he says, I put my trust in thee.

00:21:22.620 --> 00:21:24.280
Again, it's purposed.

00:21:26.020 --> 00:21:31.020
He specifically in his plea reveals to us his desire

00:21:31.220 --> 00:21:32.420
to not be ashamed.

00:21:32.420 --> 00:21:34.340
But in verse number 20, notice what he says,

00:21:34.340 --> 00:21:39.340
oh, keep my soul, keep my soul.

00:21:39.900 --> 00:21:44.620
He says in verse number 20, deliver me, deliver me.

00:21:45.980 --> 00:21:50.860
We find that David, he is longing for peace.

00:21:50.860 --> 00:21:55.340
He's trusting that the Lord and only the Lord

00:21:55.340 --> 00:22:00.340
can provide for him the peace that he's longing for.

00:22:00.420 --> 00:22:04.760
We see that he's trusting, verse two, I mentioned already.

00:22:04.760 --> 00:22:08.260
Verse number 20, verse 21, he says again

00:22:08.260 --> 00:22:10.620
at the end of verse 21, I wait on thee.

00:22:10.620 --> 00:22:13.100
He had mentioned that in verse number three.

00:22:13.100 --> 00:22:16.180
So we begin to see how David is longing for peace,

00:22:16.180 --> 00:22:18.900
but he's trusting the Lord to provide it.

00:22:18.900 --> 00:22:21.760
This evening, it's important that we acknowledge

00:22:21.760 --> 00:22:23.820
as we study this text of scripture

00:22:23.820 --> 00:22:27.260
and look at the distress and the desire of David

00:22:27.260 --> 00:22:30.060
that he's longing for peace and he knows

00:22:30.060 --> 00:22:33.220
that only God can provide that peace.

00:22:33.220 --> 00:22:34.660
And I just wonder tonight,

00:22:35.900 --> 00:22:37.660
is there some trouble in your life?

00:22:38.540 --> 00:22:41.460
Some difficulty where you just need peace?

00:22:42.260 --> 00:22:45.420
You understand that there's this trouble

00:22:45.420 --> 00:22:49.740
that's just stirring and it's just an unfortunate situation.

00:22:49.740 --> 00:22:51.460
Maybe there's some circumstances

00:22:51.460 --> 00:22:53.520
such as what David was facing here.

00:22:53.520 --> 00:22:55.720
There's plenty of times that David did things

00:22:55.720 --> 00:22:57.880
that brought trouble on his own,

00:22:57.880 --> 00:23:01.720
but we find there are times in which the trouble comes

00:23:01.720 --> 00:23:04.260
and we could argue this evening with regard

00:23:04.260 --> 00:23:08.540
to how David handled the situation with Absalom

00:23:08.540 --> 00:23:10.540
and leading up to the revolt.

00:23:10.540 --> 00:23:13.540
And yes, there were certainly issues on his side

00:23:13.540 --> 00:23:16.060
that he could have handled differently

00:23:16.060 --> 00:23:17.220
and we could deal with that,

00:23:17.220 --> 00:23:21.180
but we find that David in this moment of difficulty,

00:23:21.180 --> 00:23:24.300
of chaos, he's longing for peace.

00:23:26.280 --> 00:23:27.120
Peace.

00:23:28.400 --> 00:23:32.980
So often, we think, and I know that I've said it before,

00:23:32.980 --> 00:23:36.620
that peace can be found in the absence of trouble.

00:23:37.820 --> 00:23:39.580
The reality is that peace is found

00:23:39.580 --> 00:23:41.740
in the person of Jesus Christ.

00:23:42.540 --> 00:23:44.620
The trouble can rage all around you.

00:23:44.620 --> 00:23:47.080
It can rage all around me.

00:23:47.080 --> 00:23:49.340
We can have peace.

00:23:49.340 --> 00:23:51.460
We can have peace,

00:23:51.460 --> 00:23:56.460
knowing that we've put our trust in the Lord.

00:23:56.660 --> 00:24:01.660
And we're trusting that God will do what only God can do.

00:24:01.880 --> 00:24:04.020
Notice, if you will, turn to the book of Philippians

00:24:04.020 --> 00:24:07.660
and then we'll make one last reference to Psalm 25

00:24:07.660 --> 00:24:09.540
before we have our prayer time this evening.

00:24:09.540 --> 00:24:13.340
But look, if you will, in Philippians chapter number four.

00:24:13.340 --> 00:24:15.580
Philippians four is a great text of scripture

00:24:15.580 --> 00:24:19.120
dealing with the subject matter of peace.

00:24:21.980 --> 00:24:26.500
We find that Paul writing here to these believers

00:24:26.500 --> 00:24:28.460
in Philippi at the church there

00:24:28.460 --> 00:24:32.060
that God enabled him to have a part in starting

00:24:32.060 --> 00:24:34.820
and he's speaking to them from prison,

00:24:34.820 --> 00:24:36.180
writing to them from prison.

00:24:36.180 --> 00:24:37.900
He says in verse number four,

00:24:37.900 --> 00:24:40.300
rejoice in the Lord always.

00:24:40.300 --> 00:24:44.060
And again, I say, rejoice.

00:24:44.060 --> 00:24:46.700
Let your moderation be known unto all men.

00:24:46.700 --> 00:24:49.180
The Lord is at hand.

00:24:49.180 --> 00:24:52.420
Verse six, be careful for nothing,

00:24:52.420 --> 00:24:54.980
but in everything by prayer and supplication

00:24:54.980 --> 00:24:59.980
with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known unto God.

00:25:00.960 --> 00:25:02.940
And the peace of God,

00:25:03.780 --> 00:25:06.580
which passeth all understanding,

00:25:06.580 --> 00:25:11.580
shall keep your hearts and minds through Christ Jesus.

00:25:12.260 --> 00:25:14.500
Aren't you thankful for verse number seven?

00:25:15.940 --> 00:25:18.200
When you begin to look at in their times

00:25:18.200 --> 00:25:20.260
in which maybe we'll read verse seven

00:25:20.260 --> 00:25:23.440
or maybe we'll quote Philippians four seven

00:25:23.440 --> 00:25:26.140
without looking at the greater context of it.

00:25:26.140 --> 00:25:31.140
But we find this evening that what God is saying

00:25:31.180 --> 00:25:34.040
through Paul to these believers in Philippi,

00:25:34.040 --> 00:25:39.040
rejoice, rejoice in the Lord always.

00:25:39.340 --> 00:25:40.180
Right?

00:25:40.180 --> 00:25:43.780
Listen, are there times in which it's easier to rejoice?

00:25:43.780 --> 00:25:46.660
There are times in which it's difficult to rejoice?

00:25:46.660 --> 00:25:47.820
We live in this world.

00:25:47.820 --> 00:25:49.380
You face difficulties.

00:25:49.380 --> 00:25:50.740
I understand.

00:25:50.740 --> 00:25:52.560
There are times in which it's hard.

00:25:52.560 --> 00:25:54.740
You say, in everything give thanks.

00:25:54.740 --> 00:25:57.340
And you say, maybe I'm struggling in this thing.

00:25:57.340 --> 00:25:58.860
I know this is God's will.

00:25:58.860 --> 00:26:00.780
I know he wants me to rejoice,

00:26:01.420 --> 00:26:02.260
but I'm struggling.

00:26:02.260 --> 00:26:04.620
And Paul says, rejoice in the Lord always.

00:26:04.620 --> 00:26:06.100
And again, I say rejoice.

00:26:06.100 --> 00:26:08.220
Let your moderation be known unto all men.

00:26:08.220 --> 00:26:09.600
The Lord is at hand.

00:26:09.600 --> 00:26:11.500
And then he tells them in verse number six,

00:26:11.500 --> 00:26:13.180
be careful for nothing.

00:26:13.180 --> 00:26:15.580
Literally worry about nothing.

00:26:16.660 --> 00:26:19.200
We could park there for weeks.

00:26:19.200 --> 00:26:20.580
Could we not?

00:26:20.580 --> 00:26:22.600
Worry, worry.

00:26:23.700 --> 00:26:28.580
We, some of us have gotten to a place where we say,

00:26:28.580 --> 00:26:31.300
we've removed the word from our vocabulary

00:26:31.300 --> 00:26:34.020
so that it doesn't look too bad to others.

00:26:34.020 --> 00:26:36.500
And we don't say, I'm worried about this

00:26:36.500 --> 00:26:39.100
because we know that we're not supposed to worry.

00:26:39.100 --> 00:26:41.720
And so we might say, this really concerns me.

00:26:43.500 --> 00:26:45.820
We just try to change our vocabulary a little bit,

00:26:45.820 --> 00:26:47.540
but really, what are we saying?

00:26:47.540 --> 00:26:49.880
I'm worried about this.

00:26:49.880 --> 00:26:50.720
Right?

00:26:53.460 --> 00:26:55.340
Be careful for nothing.

00:26:56.340 --> 00:27:00.680
Worry is not gonna fix anything.

00:27:02.020 --> 00:27:04.260
Worry is bad for you.

00:27:05.620 --> 00:27:08.000
Not only did God tell us not to worry,

00:27:08.000 --> 00:27:13.000
but physiologically, what it does to you when you worry

00:27:13.660 --> 00:27:15.300
is bad.

00:27:15.300 --> 00:27:16.540
It's bad for your health.

00:27:20.060 --> 00:27:23.840
Instead of worrying in everything,

00:27:23.840 --> 00:27:28.840
by prayer and supplication with thanksgiving,

00:27:29.020 --> 00:27:32.520
let your requests be made known unto God.

00:27:32.520 --> 00:27:37.320
Isn't it so much more productive to pray

00:27:37.320 --> 00:27:40.520
and to thank God than to try to worry?

00:27:41.680 --> 00:27:43.160
You say, but worry is natural.

00:27:43.160 --> 00:27:43.980
I understand.

00:27:43.980 --> 00:27:47.120
That's why God says be careful for nothing.

00:27:47.120 --> 00:27:50.040
Because it's natural response for us.

00:27:50.040 --> 00:27:52.920
We deal with a situation, a circumstance.

00:27:52.920 --> 00:27:55.720
There's this unknown, and we begin to worry about it,

00:27:55.720 --> 00:27:59.160
and it just consumes us, and it controls us,

00:27:59.160 --> 00:28:03.960
and we see that here, the Lord says, don't worry,

00:28:03.960 --> 00:28:06.360
but instead, pray.

00:28:06.360 --> 00:28:08.480
Aren't you thankful to know the God

00:28:08.480 --> 00:28:10.680
who hears and answers prayer?

00:28:10.680 --> 00:28:13.920
I was reading in my Bible reading this morning,

00:28:13.920 --> 00:28:17.920
and I don't know how many times I've read the Bible.

00:28:17.920 --> 00:28:18.760
I really don't.

00:28:18.760 --> 00:28:20.160
I never kept track of it.

00:28:20.160 --> 00:28:22.600
I typically read at least twice a year.

00:28:23.280 --> 00:28:27.240
I'm gonna do two times a year this year for 2025,

00:28:27.240 --> 00:28:29.600
in addition to some other things that I do,

00:28:29.600 --> 00:28:32.040
but there have been some times in the past

00:28:32.040 --> 00:28:35.320
that not only reading through the Bible twice in a year,

00:28:35.320 --> 00:28:38.600
but I also would read the book of Psalms every month,

00:28:38.600 --> 00:28:41.000
and so I'd read the book of Psalms 12 times in the year,

00:28:41.000 --> 00:28:42.600
plus I'd read the Bible twice,

00:28:42.600 --> 00:28:44.700
and I read something this morning

00:28:44.700 --> 00:28:47.239
that I felt like I never saw before.

00:28:47.239 --> 00:28:48.760
Has that ever happened to you?

00:28:49.679 --> 00:28:51.520
I don't know how many times I've read it,

00:28:51.520 --> 00:28:53.960
but it just kind of hit me today when I read it,

00:28:53.960 --> 00:28:56.679
and it was so encouraging to my heart,

00:28:56.679 --> 00:29:00.720
and I was like, Lord, I know I've read that verse

00:29:00.720 --> 00:29:03.000
many, many times,

00:29:03.000 --> 00:29:05.800
but it's almost like I never saw it before,

00:29:05.800 --> 00:29:07.640
and in Psalm 99 in verse number six,

00:29:07.640 --> 00:29:08.800
you don't need to turn there,

00:29:08.800 --> 00:29:09.640
but the Bible says,

00:29:09.640 --> 00:29:11.640
Moses and Aaron among his priest,

00:29:11.640 --> 00:29:14.320
and Samuel among them that call upon his name,

00:29:14.320 --> 00:29:19.320
they called upon the Lord, and he answered them.

00:29:20.320 --> 00:29:21.840
I love it.

00:29:21.840 --> 00:29:25.160
So often we quote Jeremiah 33 in verse number three,

00:29:25.160 --> 00:29:26.000
and we should.

00:29:26.000 --> 00:29:26.880
It's a great verse.

00:29:26.880 --> 00:29:27.760
It's a great promise.

00:29:27.760 --> 00:29:29.960
Call unto me, and I will answer thee,

00:29:29.960 --> 00:29:31.480
and show thee great and mighty things,

00:29:31.480 --> 00:29:32.640
which thou knowest not,

00:29:32.640 --> 00:29:35.200
but we find there in Psalm 99 in verse number six

00:29:35.200 --> 00:29:39.040
where God says they called, and I answered.

00:29:39.040 --> 00:29:43.300
Praise God, and so prayer works.

00:29:43.300 --> 00:29:45.119
Worry is bad for you.

00:29:45.119 --> 00:29:48.160
Prayer works, and he says,

00:29:48.160 --> 00:29:49.720
let your request be made,

00:29:49.720 --> 00:29:51.720
he says, sorry, be careful for nothing,

00:29:51.720 --> 00:29:54.200
but in everything by prayer and supplication

